{
  "texts": [
    "Two binary classification tasks are performed on these tokens, and the middle part of the BERT output is utilized for token classification.",
    "The results of the first step are then subjected to multi-label classification, with BERT used again as the backbone.",
    "Compared to TAS-BERT in Table 8, the Extract-Classify-ACOS method first extracts the aspects and opinions and predicts the implicit ones before performing ACOS classification.",
    "Extract-Classify-ACOS enables it better to identify implicit aspects and opinions in the text.",
    "Therefore, for these implicit aspects and opinions, the method can classify them correctly into their corresponding ACOS categories, thereby improving the overall accuracy."
  ]
}